Description: An implementation of the multidimensional Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS) two-sample test described by Fasano and Franceschini (1987) <doi:10.1093/mnras/225.1.155>. The 'fasano.franceschini.test' package provides three major improvements over the current multidimensional KS test on the Comprehensive R Archive Network (CRAN): (i) the computation of the test statistic has a log-linear rather than cubic time complexity; (ii) testing in arbitrary dimensions rather than just two or three; and (iii) a parallelized permutation procedure for rapid significance testing. Ultimately, the 'fasano.franceschini.test' package presents a robust statistical test for analyzing random samples defined in multiple dimensions.
